The paper discusses the use of network visualization programs and geographic mapping tools to analyze the distribution patterns and networks of relations among addresses in scientific publications. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), software development (cs.SD), and computer systems and technology (cs.CY). However, given the focus on bibliometric analysis and citation databases, cs.DL and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories.
